{"title_page": "Taiwanese whisky", "text_new": "Taiwanese whisky is whisky made in [[Taiwan]]. The most prominent Taiwanese whisky producer is the [[Kavalan Distillery]]. In 2015 the Kavalan Solist Vinho Barrique was named the best single malt whisky in the world at the World Whiskies Awards.<ref>{{cite web |title=The world\u2019s best whisky? It comes from Taiwan |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/foodanddrinknews/11490228/The-worlds-best-whisky-It-comes-from-Taiwan.html |website=www.telegraph.co.uk |publisher=The Telegraph |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC 2015\" >{{cite web |last1=Kai-Hwa Wang |first1=Frances |title=The Best Single Malt Whiskey in the World Is From Taiwan |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/best-single-malt-whiskey-world-taiwan-n332521 |website=www.nbcnews.com |publisher=NBC News |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> A significant whisky market, Taiwan is the third largest consumer of single malts in the world.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Kavalan Distillery Second Distillation Plant \u5676\u746a\u862d\u9152\u5ee0 \u84b8\u993e\u4e8c\u5ee0.jpg|thumb|Kavalan Distillery Second Distillation Plant \u5676\u746a\u862d\u9152\u5ee0 \u84b8\u993e\u4e8c\u5ee0]]\nTaiwanese whisky first gained prominence in 2011 when a Taiwanese whisky beat three Scotches and an English whisky at Scotland\u2019s Burns Night.<ref name=\"CNN 2017\" >{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Marian |title=How a Taiwanese whisky became a global favorite |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/taiwan-whisky-kavalan/index.html |website=www.cnn.com |publisher=CNN |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> In 2015 the Kavalan Solist Vinho Barrique was named the best single malt whisky in the world at the World Whiskies Awards.<ref name=\"NBC 2015\" /> Seeking to imitate Kavalan\u2019s success the government owned [[Taiwan Tobacco and Liquor Corporation]] who had long ago abandoned whisky production entered the market with the Omar brand.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jennings |first1=Ralph |title=Subtropical Taiwan Suddenly Boasts Two World-Renowned Brands Of Whiskey |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ralphjennings/2018/09/26/subtropical-taiwan-suddenly-boasts-two-world-renowned-brands-of-whiskey/#36300a814a4f |website=www.forbes.com |publisher=Forbes |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Styles==\nAs it is a young producer there is no standard style for Taiwanese whisky dictated either by law or tradition leaving producers free to experiment and innovate.<ref name=\"CNN 2017\" /> Due to Taiwan\u2019s [[subtropical]] climate whisky matures two to three times as fast as it would in Scotland or Ireland. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Quinn |first1=Martin |title=How Taiwan became a global powerhouse in whisky production |url=https://theconversation.com/how-taiwan-became-a-global-powerhouse-in-whisky-production-123808 |website=theconversation.com |publisher=The Conversation |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> Taiwanese whisky often has notes of subtropical fruit and in general have a creamy character however there is quite a bit of variation.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Centrone |first1=Ian |title=How Taiwan Became a World-Class Whisky Region |url=https://www.tastingtable.com/dine/national/best-whisky-regions-taiwan-kavalan |website=www.tastingtable.com |publisher=Tasting Table |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==As a market==\nTaiwan has a developed and sophisticated whisky market. Taiwan is the third largest market for single malt whisky after the US and France.<ref name=\"CNN 2017\" /> [[Pernod Ricard]] has described the Taiwanese whisky market as \u201cdiscerning and advanced\u201d and has produced special edition whiskies for the Taiwanese market.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Coleman |first1=Liam |title=The Glenlivet honours Taiwan whisky market with Taoyuan Airport exclusive |url=https://www.moodiedavittreport.com/the-glenlivet-honours-taiwan-whisky-market-with-taoyuan-airport-exclusive/ |website=www.moodiedavittreport.com |publisher=The Moodie Davitt Report |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nTaiwan is the only whisky market which drinks more single malt whisky than blended whisky.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Koutsakis |first1=George |title=Can Taiwan\u2019s premium gin producers take on the world \u2013 and Taiwanese drinkers who prefer foreign liquor? |url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/leisure/article/3031413/can-taiwans-premium-gin-producers-take-world-and-taiwanese |website=www.scmp.com |publisher=SCMP |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Japanese whisky]]\n* [[Australian whisky]]\n* [[Indian whisky]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Whisky}}\n{{Taiwanese cuisine}}\n\n[[Category:Taiwanese whisky]]\n", "text_old": "Taiwanese whisky is whisky made in [[Taiwan]]. The most prominent Taiwanese whisky producer is the [[Kavalan Distillery]]. In 2015 the Kavalan Solist Vinho Barrique was named the best single malt whisky in the world at the World Whiskies Awards.<ref>{{cite web |title=The world\u2019s best whisky? It comes from Taiwan |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/foodanddrinknews/11490228/The-worlds-best-whisky-It-comes-from-Taiwan.html |website=www.telegraph.co.uk |publisher=The Telegraph |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC 2015\" >{{cite web |last1=Kai-Hwa Wang |first1=Frances |title=The Best Single Malt Whiskey in the World Is From Taiwan |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/best-single-malt-whiskey-world-taiwan-n332521 |website=www.nbcnews.com |publisher=NBC News |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> A significant whisky market, Taiwan is the third largest consumer of single malts in the world.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Kavalan Distillery Second Distillation Plant \u5676\u746a\u862d\u9152\u5ee0 \u84b8\u993e\u4e8c\u5ee0.jpg|thumb|Kavalan Distillery Second Distillation Plant \u5676\u746a\u862d\u9152\u5ee0 \u84b8\u993e\u4e8c\u5ee0]]\nTaiwanese whisky first gained prominence in 2011 when a Taiwanese whisky beat three Scotches and an English whisky at Scotland\u2019s Burns Night.<ref name=\"CNN 2017\" >{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Marian |title=How a Taiwanese whisky became a global favorite |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/taiwan-whisky-kavalan/index.html |website=www.cnn.com |publisher=CNN |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> In 2015 the Kavalan Solist Vinho Barrique was named the best single malt whisky in the world at the World Whiskies Awards.<ref name=\"NBC 2015\" /> Seeking to imitate Kavalan\u2019s success the government owned [[Taiwan Tobacco and Liquor Corporation]] who had long ago abandoned whisky production entered the market with the Omar brand.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jennings |first1=Ralph |title=Subtropical Taiwan Suddenly Boasts Two World-Renowned Brands Of Whiskey |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ralphjennings/2018/09/26/subtropical-taiwan-suddenly-boasts-two-world-renowned-brands-of-whiskey/#36300a814a4f |website=www.forbes.com |publisher=Forbes |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Styles==\nAs it is a young producer there is no standard style for Taiwanese whisky dictated either by law or tradition leaving producers free to experiment and innovate.<ref name=\"CNN 2017\" /> Due to Taiwan\u2019s [[subtropical]] climate whisky matures two to three times as fast as it would in Scotland or Ireland. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Quinn |first1=Martin |title=How Taiwan became a global powerhouse in whisky production |url=https://theconversation.com/how-taiwan-became-a-global-powerhouse-in-whisky-production-123808 |website=theconversation.com |publisher=The Conversation |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> Taiwanese whisky often has notes of subtropical fruit and in general have a creamy character however there is quite a bit of variation.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Centrone |first1=Ian |title=How Taiwan Became a World-Class Whisky Region |url=https://www.tastingtable.com/dine/national/best-whisky-regions-taiwan-kavalan |website=www.tastingtable.com |publisher=Tasting Table |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==As a market==\nTai